        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 11:33AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 1132 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Elk Silver, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elk Silver, Sixteen Springs, Upper Dry Burnt Canyon, Lower Sixteen
Springs Canyon, Elk Canyon, Lower Dry Burnt Canyon, Bell Canyon, and
Mescalero Apache Cow Camp One.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
